  "read": "TileLang query-major compact-final dKV producer. Each CTA owns a token/panel/D block, computes selected-row dKV contributions with TileLang MFMA, reduces them into a compact active-group table inside the CTA, then atomic-adds only those reduced compact rows directly into final [groups, D] dKV. This tests whether reduced global atomics can beat writing and later reducing a large compact partial-row stream. This run also launches a correctness-preserving TileLang spill kernel for actual-LI panel overflow pairs. The packed panel path uses original selected-slot weights, and the spill path adds the dropped original LI pairs back into final dKV.",
